<h1>Problem 158 - 2012 APMO, Q5</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Let \(n\) be an integer greater than or equal to \(2\). Prove that if the real numbers \(a_1 , a_2 , \cdots , a_n\) satisfy \(a_1 ^2 + a_2 ^2 + \cdots + a_n ^ 2 = n\), then
\[\sum_{1 \le i < j \le n} \frac{1}{n- a_i a_j}  \le \frac{n}{2}\]
must hold.</p>
